Asciidoc Syntax Related
-----------------------


Doc Title
=========

Level 1
-------

Level 2
~~~~~~~

Level 3
^^^^^^^

Level 4
+++++++

or

= Doc Title
== Level 1
=== Level 2
==== Level 3
===== Level 4

forced +
line break

To get  a blank line
{empty} +

normal, _italic_, *bold*, +mono+.
``double quoted'', `single quoted'
normal, ^super^, ~sub~

[red]#red text#
[yellow-background]#on yellow#
[big]#large#
[red yellow-background big]*all bold*

////
comment block
////

put ur src text in like this (src-highlighting for asciidoctor given below)

.title
[source,sh]
----
cp src dest
----

Escaping text
~~~~~~~~~~~~~

This escapes the otherwise bolding effect - char $$*$$p, $$*q$$;

Columish Display
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

++++
<table><tr><td>
++++

Asciidoc contents here

++++
</td><td>
++++

Next column content here

++++
</td></tr></table>
++++

Links and Images
